These files should /overwrite/ their respective counterparts in the ezquake
source.

If these instructions are incorrect (I'm writing them in a hurry) just
update this file with the correct way to do it..

To quickly get ezquake up and running "from nothing" with these files
=====================================================================
# Original quake
scp <you>@<pulia>:/mnt/irene/games/quake.zip .
unzip quake.zip && cd quake_1.01/

# Ezquake svn
svn co https://ezquake.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/ezquake/trunk ezquake

# Modified files
cd ezquake/ezquake/
git clone gitosis@<pulia>:ezquake_mods

# Use modified files
# cp ezquake_mods/* .

# Build
make

To update the modes from git
============================
cd ezquake_mods/
git pull origin master

How to commit and push to pulia
===============================
git pull origin master                        # make sure you're up-to-date
git commit -a -m "A description your changes" # commit
git push origin master                        # upload
